99
00:03:56,035 --> 00:03:58,196
You can't ship a game with anything TBD, right?

100
00:03:58,196 --> 00:04:00,918
When you ship a game, you have made every single decision

101
00:04:00,918 --> 00:04:03,600
and you've decided every single aspect of every feature,

102
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:06,702
every character, every single thing in your game.

103
00:04:06,702 --> 00:04:09,123
Even in live games, if you're doing regular releases,

104
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:11,064
you have to decide every single aspect

105
00:04:11,064 --> 00:04:13,586
of every single thing that goes into each release, right?

106
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:16,048
So you can only ship when all of the ambiguity is gone.

