00:04:26,386 --> 00:04:27,366
Oh, one person.

110
00:04:27,366 --> 00:04:28,767
Okay, awesome.

111
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:28,967
Yeah.

112
00:04:28,967 --> 00:04:34,529
Since 2001, I've worked at seven studios, I've shipped a dozen games, and I've worked

113
00:04:34,529 --> 00:04:35,609
on a project like that once.

114
00:04:37,038 --> 00:04:39,079
And that makes sense because most of us

115
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:40,900
get into game development because we wanna innovate,

116
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,481
right, we wanna make awesome new things.

117
00:04:42,481 --> 00:04:44,482
And when you're innovating is exactly

118
00:04:44,482 --> 00:04:45,743
when you have the most ambiguity

119
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:47,064
because you're doing something new,

120
