00:06:45,584 --> 00:06:49,365
In this talk, I want to talk about some of the problems that arise from really ambiguous

175
00:06:49,365 --> 00:06:58,846
situations and what you as the producer can do to either solve these problems or avoid

176
00:06:58,846 --> 00:07:00,607
them before they happen.

177
00:07:01,597 --> 00:07:08,060
Again, because ambiguity is something that all of us are going to face on almost every

178
00:07:08,060 --> 00:07:12,302
project, so if you can get really good at dealing gracefully with it, you are going

179
00:07:12,302 --> 00:07:16,024
to be a really valuable producer and a better producer.

180
00:07:16,024 --> 00:07:19,225
So as a producer, your job is to make sure the right work gets done.

181
00:07:19,225 --> 00:07:19,905
Okay?

182
00:07:19,905 --> 00:07:21,686
This is basic project management.

183
00:07:21,686 --> 00:07:24,227
Make sure that the right work is getting done.

184
00:07:25,909 --> 00:07:31,212
The number one thing that my team looks for when hiring project managers is the ability

185
00:07:31,212 --> 00:07:32,773
to deal gracefully with ambiguity.

186
00:07:32,773 --> 00:07:36,555
Because as producers, there's a lot of things that we can do to manage this uncertainty.

187
00:07:36,555 --> 00:07:39,096
And really, it's kind of the core of our job.

188
00:07:39,096 --> 00:07:41,758
Because this is what your job is as a producer, right?

189
00:07:41,758 --> 00:07:45,580
So prioritization, you know, if you're trying to make sure the right work gets done, you

190
00:07:45,580 --> 00:07:47,541
need to make sure that your team knows what the right work is.

191
00:07:49,357 --> 00:07:55,038
Driving decisions, making sure that the right work is defined when it needs to be, and gathering the information that people need to define

192
00:07:55,038 --> 00:07:56,018
which is the right work.

193
00:07:56,018 --> 00:08:02,000
Scheduling and tasking, communicating what the right work is to people, making sure that everyone knows who's doing it, and

194
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:07,141
making sure that the things are getting, you know, that are being worked on when they need to be.

195
00:08:07,141 --> 00:08:11,942
And then owning deadlines, so making sure that work gets done, and making sure everyone understands what done means.

196
00:08:13,497 --> 00:08:14,377
So this is your job.

197
00:08:14,377 --> 00:08:16,317
Now, on super ambiguous projects,

198
00:08:16,317 --> 00:08:19,518
you can get into this kind of worst case scenario state

199
00:08:19,518 --> 00:08:24,199
